# 📊 User Behavior & Retention Analysis (E-commerce)

## 🚀 Project Overview

This project analyzes user behavior and retention patterns for an e-commerce platform similar to Stylenhomes.

The goal is to identify:

* Why users do not return
* Which users generate the most value
* How to improve repeat purchases

---

## 🎯 Business Problem

The platform is facing:

* Low repeat purchase rate
* High drop-off after first purchase

This analysis focuses on improving **customer retention and lifetime value (LTV)**.

---

## 📂 Dataset

Synthetic dataset with 10,000+ rows including:

* user_id
* session_id
* timestamp
* product_id
* category
* action (view, cart, purchase)
* session_duration

---

## 🔍 Key Analysis

### 1. User Behavior Analysis

* New vs Returning Users
* Session behavior patterns
* Time spent vs conversion

### 2. Retention Analysis

* Cohort analysis based on first purchase
* Retention rate over time

### 3. User Segmentation

* One-time buyers
* Frequent users
* High-value users

---

## 📊 Dashboard

The dashboard includes:

* Retention curve
* Conversion trends
* User segmentation
* KPI metrics (conversion rate, repeat purchase rate)

---

## 📈 Key Insights

* Majority of users are one-time buyers
* Longer sessions lead to higher conversions
* Repeat users contribute significantly higher revenue

---

## 💡 Recommendations

* Improve onboarding for first-time users
* Introduce retention campaigns (email/discounts)
* Optimize product pages to increase engagement

---

## 🛠 Tools Used

* Python (Pandas, Matplotlib)
* SQL
* Tableau / Power BI

